Thats prety confrontatonal, PO, I think Yales said that nobody was harmed.  This, however, was a test case.  They INTENDED to blow up the engine, to see what would happen.  They deliberately took safety measures and performed the test in a location and under conditions where it would have no significant negative effects.  In a real life launch, those situations would not be mirrored.  You would HAVE to have a ground crew nearby.  You would have pilots onboard.  People WOULD die if a similar accident occured in an operational system.<br>
